Zwelinzima Vavi, General Secretary of the South African Federation of Trade Unions. AFP/John Wessels JOHANNESBURG - Saftu and its affiliates have come together in a show of solidarity with General-Secretary Zwelinzima Vavi.
The unions say they reject the notice of intent to suspend Vavi and want him to continue his work. READ: Saftu seeks to suspend Zwelinzima Vavi Vavi is being probed for alleged financial and administrative violations.
The Saftu leadership says the investigation will also include allegations that Vavi disrespected or undermined constitutional structures and resolutions.  Some Saftu affiliates have come together in a show of solidarity with General-Secretary Zwelinzima Vavi. The unions say they reject the notice of intent to suspend Vavi and want him to continue his work. He is being probed for alleged financial and administrative violations. pic.twitter.com/d3zVCNZvfi